    "title": "Run constant-time tests as part of test suite (except on rare platforms to be problematic)",
    "body": "See discussions here:\r\n - https://gnusha.org/secp256k1/2024-07-01.log \r\n - https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/issues/1549\r\n\r\nWe want to exclude problematic platforms to address the concerns in https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/pull/723 .\r\n\r\nRare platforms that were problematic in the past are\r\n -  [s390](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/issues/784),\r\n -  [power9](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/pull/708#issuecomment-573453603) (also http://gnusha.org/secp256k1/2020-01-11.log at 11:29 and 11:37 ) \r\n\r\nBut all of these reports are old, in particular the second one is for the old ECDH code. It may be a good idea to start with an empty list and see if we'll actually get reports.",
